== The Beginning of All Things
=== The First Age
In the beginning, all four elemental planes met at a place called The Conflux.
- To its North: the plane of Earth,
- To its South: the plain of Air,
- To its west: Fire,
- To its East: Water.

The infinite planes were home to all beings who called upon their power. Mortals, immortals, even the gods.

At the Conflux, all mana mingled in a vortex of pure magic.

This, although not acknowledged by many human scholars, was the *First Age*.

Within the First Age came all most all of the mortal races, most notably without the humans.

=== The Second Age
The Second Age began when a group of gods, only known as The Five, pushed apart the elemental planes. Using the power contained within the Conflux, they created a material realm to be their play thing.

Six thousand years of war followed.

The Five created new species with which to war, and appeared to their chosen ones to start holy wars anew whenever the excitement waned.

Their most dangerous and long lived creation was humans. They spread quickly, inventing a nd building much in their short lives.

At the end of the Second Age, six powerful witches and wizards, The Wilds, gathered and banished The Five from the realms. Locking them behind the Celestial Gate never to influence the planes again.

The realm The Five had created was allowed to settle, and its people grow beyond the drive for war.

They eventually came to call this realm *Thalassa*.

