#v(3cm)
=== The Third Age
During the Third Age, realms were carved out and teritories settled. Immoren, the largest continent, now homes the elven nation of Ios, the dwarven kingdoms that form Rhûl and the human nations of Cygnar, Khador and Ord.

Continuing in the traditions of war, Cygnar and Khador have spent much of this age in some form of conflict.

Ord has only maintained its neutrality by an artifact of the Wilds' spell. The sealing of the Celestial Gate has left Ord completely devoid of natural mana. It is, without trade, completely magicless.

=== The Fourth Age
Around 18 months ago, something strange happened. A huge surge of magic pulsed into Thalassa from every plane, as if they were collapsing in on one another.

This has caused chaos around the world.
- Devices using matic went haywire or shattered.
- The city of Dalaran nearly crashed into the sea.
- Injuries and damages caused all over the world from spells gone awry.
 
Most curiously, a large number of people born magicless have now discovered that they can sense and channel mana!

This has brought about significant change in every nation, and is being discussed as:
==== The Convergence, Herald of the Fourth Age
And this is where our adventure begins.

