== The tale of \_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_\_
The Swooping Gull had broken with about as much effort as tearing paper. Snapped cleanly in half by a giant wave, part water, part mana. The Convergence was not kind to those at sea.

It didn't take long before you were so deep that the light couldn't reach you. Without the screams of the crew and the choking smoke, it was almost peaceful. Well, until your lungs started to burn.

Beginning to panic, you started to look around for any clue as to which way was up. This deep, you couldn't tell. Begging for help, screaming with your final thoughts into the depths, you noticed something shifting below you.

A bright yellow orb, glowing like the moon, openned. It dawned on you that this was a single, giant, eye. The rest of the creature was impossible to make out in the depth. Sinuous, scaled and unknowably long.

As your vision faded, last breath long spent, you heard one word, spoken directly into your mind.

==== *L I V E*


You awoke on the shore near Highgate port, some 3 days sail from the Shattered Coast where the ship sank. The entire experience felt like a fading dream almost immediately, leaving you with just the unnerving sensation of being watched. 

Somehow, you know its name. *Kaga a'al*. The name of a god. A saviour of the drowned. You have dedicated your life to its worship ever since that day. If only it would communicate with you clearly, you may understand its wishes.

==== The adventure begins
Finding yourself in Highgate, a port you are familiar with, although now you stride through it with a purpose. To find those in need and save them, just as Kaga a'al saved you. 

To begin with, the guards don't seem to take too kindly to that. So you begin to seek out other tales. Taverns seem only too happy to put you in a room and feed you, although you do get a few scowls if you stay in one place too long.

Within The Three Lemons, a particularly nice tarvern for the evening, you heard tale of something strange going on in Nestowe. The village is not far from here, and famed for its sparkling wines. The guards are apparently disinterested in helping, so it could be a perfect opportunity to go and spread the word.

Packing a few days provisions, generously given by a provisioner by the dock, you head off towards Nestowe.


#pagebreak()
== The tale of Vanwe
Rael lies on the border of Ios and the mysterious Bloodstone Marshes. Many rumours about things in the mists exist, but when one baby was born it shocked its parents so much they decided to take the risk.

Nestled within a stump, a tiny half-elf was left to the wilds.
::
Three days later, you walked into Rael, from the  path those parents trod. You, with the baby's name. You, with memories of the childhood stolen from a babe. You remember your father weeping when his brother died. You remember the shared joy of your mother's graduation.

None of these things have come to pass yet, but you remember them none the less.

The people of Rael have been, considering, very accomodating. And, while you family are uncomfortable with discussions of the future, they have taken you in.

Determined to learn more about what happened, you sought the help of the Mages Guild in Rael. They, in turn, have suggested you investigate records within the Mages Guild in Highgate.

==== The adventure begins
Shortly before you arrived in Highgate, you felt a surge of energy that pulsed through the world. While it put you on edge, it didn't seem to impact the shadows. That is to say, the Fey Wild didn't disturb. Its denizens certainly would have noticed, however.

You now know this to be the Convergence, and it has put a bump in your path to discovering more about yourself. When you arrived at the Highgate Mages Guild, there was no way that you would be granted access. The whole Guild had been mobilised throughout the city to deal with the impact of the Convergence, and they will be busy for some time afterwards too.

Seeking more information out yourself, you heard rumours from Nestowe. It seems they've reported strange happenings in their fields. Nobody has been hurt, or remembers seeing anything, but things are going missing.

While it's not a one on one with a Fey specialist within the guild, this seems like a good place to start your search.

