== The Tale of Rynella Tykarys
==== Celestial Gatekeeping: An Arcane Analysis of Restorative Magics
A bold title, but the Guild likes that. No consideration for the clerics it will irritate, but they probably won't read it anyway.

Being born with purple skin, horns and a tail was certainly a suprise to your very definitely human parents, but they adapted well. Mostly by fire-retarding everything.

Always interested in how things work, never satisfied with a "it's just like that" answer, the Engineers' Guild in Highgate was a natural choice.

Being told that restorative magics were for the clergy and couldn't be taught was like a red flag to a bull. Your research has already disproved that, but it has certainly ruffled some political feathers.

When you suggested that field research may be necessary to further your work, the Guilds board accepted. Perhaps a little too fast, but your research is all that matters.

==== The adventure begins

Highgate is a highly diverse city. Growing up was relitavely peaceful. Even with purple skin. Even the slick, glossy black horns didn't get in the way much.

In school, inquisitiveness was rewarded, your study supported and experimental apparatus provided. Often then replaced too when things were used 'enthusiastically'.

After a few visits, talks and an interview, your application to Highgate's Engineers' Guild was sponsored by Lei & Mei, highgates' Alchemy and Enchanting experts. Once you began with the guild, you only really stopped to sleep, normally eating at a workbench and often forgetting the sleep.

Having completed the vast majority of the available courses, many research projects and hundreds of experiments, there's little else for you at the guild. The thirst for knowledge has started to make you twitchy.

Once you had decided to leave, preparations took less than a week. Provisions gathered, guild fees paid for the next two months and your research authomaton upgraded for rigorous activity, and you're ready to stride out! But where though?

You headed to Lei & Mei's Emporium, and they suggested you head to Nestow, a village only a few days walk away.

Something strange has been reported, but details are light and the Highgate guards aren't planning to act or investigate.

Seems like  a chance to itch that curiosity, at least.
