== The Tale of Rhed
Growing up in the eyries north of Khador, you formed a special connection with the elements and the world around you. Trained by Daul, a small old ravenoid, you grew your connection to the life around you. 

You used this to help your people survive. Without much other than rock, that balance is both protected and valued. Hunting carefully in different locations, ensuring the right foods were present for species to return, safekeeping their breeding cycles. 

By the time you were four, along with Daul, you helped to keep this balance for all of the people living in the mountain villages. You acted as ambassador to your people when the Khadorian traders travelled up the slopes, as well as when the Ashari people ventured south from the Plane of Earth.

During your training, Daul helped you forge a bond with a woodland spirit, *Wren*. They have no real name, as with many Fey creatures, but have chosen to respond to this name, as they like the imagery it conjures. By developing your bond with Wren, you have felt the connection between yourself and the woods deepening.

==== The adventure begins
When it occured, you were in the sparse woods in the mountain valleys, stalking prey. Something felt wrong, and Wren became sluggish for a moment. Then came the burst of mana you now know to be The Convergence.

Startled, you rushed back to the village to find everyone OK. Confused, certainly, but OK. Daul then asked for you to check with the Ashari, as the disturbance came from the direction of their villages.

The scene at the first Ashari village you came to was far bleaker. With much of their way of life tied to the magics of the Plane of Earth, many personal belongings had been destroyed, violently shattering during the influx of mana. Many in the village were nursing wounds, and all they could do was ask you to check with the other villages.

You saw several small villages in similar disarray. Nobody had been seriously hurt, but several would bear superficial scars. Eventually you came to the largest Ashari village and found the Elder there, Shaan.

She was able to confirm much of what you had felt already. The Convergence did not begin with a surge of mana, but rather the opposite. The Plane had been pushed away, then like a breaking dam it came crashing back. 

She asked, apologising that she could not send her own people, for you to venture into the human lands to learn of what had passed. Surely some of the mages in Cygnar or Dalaran could help.

Dalaran would be a length journey, so you began with Cygnar. Travelling to Highgate on the southern coast you found a Mage guild in disarray. Even weeks after the Convergence, they were still dealing with myriad different issues caused by it.

You quickly realised that if you wanted answers, you would need to look for clues yourself. You overheard a few dock workers mentioning a delay to their shipments from Nestowe, some kind of strange disturbance that the guards wanted no part of.

Without a better clue for now, you set off out of the city. At least both you and Wren do feel more comfortable in the countryside.

