  == Spirit Totem
  You can call ask Wren to take a more tangible, visible form for a limited amount of time. Doing so is taxing, however, so Wren can only do this *once per short or long rest*.

  As a bonus action, you can summon Wren to a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Wren creates an aura in a 30-foot radius. As a bonus action, you can have Wren move up to 60 feet to another point you can see. Wren can only maintain this form for up to a minute, or until you are incapacitated.

  When using this feature, you can ask Wren to adopt one of the following forms:

  === Bear Spirit
  Wren takes the form of a bear, bolstering your allies. Each creature of your choice in the aura when Wren appears gains temporary hit points equal to 5 + your druid level. In addition, you and your allies gain advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws when within the aura.

